[src:phpunit/assertions-p02] Reports an error identified by `$message` if `$actual` is not of type `numeric`.
[src:phpunit/assertions-p02] `assertIsNotNumeric()` is the inverse of this assertion and takes the same arguments.
[src:phpunit/assertions-p02] Reports an error identified by `$message` if `$actual` is not of type `object`.
[src:phpunit/assertions-p02] `assertIsNotObject()` is the inverse of this assertion and takes the same arguments.
[src:phpunit/assertions-p02] Reports an error identified by `$message` if `$actual` is not of type `resource`.
[src:phpunit/assertions-p02] `assertIsNotResource()` is the inverse of this assertion and takes the same arguments.
[src:phpunit/assertions-p02] `assertIsClosedResource()` (and `assertIsNotClosedResource()`) are provided to explicitly check for closed resources.
[src:phpunit/assertions-p02] Reports an error identified by `$message` if `$actual` is not of type `scalar`.
[src:phpunit/assertions-p02] `assertIsNotScalar()` is the inverse of this assertion and takes the same arguments.
[src:phpunit/assertions-p02] Reports an error identified by `$message` if `$actual` is not of type `string`.
